 The Opportunity 
The Product Owner of Conversation Artificial Intelligence & Chatbots is a key member of the digital transformation efforts at Ally! The PO will lead a squad in the delivery of virtual assistant-like functionality in a variety of channels to simplify the digital experience. The Digital PO will be a strong, strategic and collaborative leader with a background in agile delivery. The PO will need to work across the enterprise to develop user stories, maintain and groom the backlog and effectively communicate prioritization and delivery impacts. The PO will need to understand the value proposition of the technology, work with UXD and VOC to understand how the technology fits into web, mobile and other customer facing applications, assess dependencies of other agile lanes and partner well with suppliers to impact technology roadmaps. The PO will be the product expert of conversational AI and Chatbots at Ally and will work strategically and tactically to deliver best in class conversation AI experiences. 
The Work Itself 
 Developing the digital roadmap and strategy of Conversational AI in partnership with business partners and stakeholders, and then break the roadmap down to a deliverable workstream specific to the PO's agile scrum squad. 
 Demonstrate product economics and value proposition 
 Ensure all regulatory and legal requires while creating an innovative and leading best in class technology 
 Driving product planning, business reviews, supplier management activities with all key partners 
 Translate digital transformation strategies to deliverable and executable tasks for the squad 
 Maintain and groom the product backlog, and communicate priorities to all impacted partners and the squad 
 Create and manage to specific and measurable success levers 
 Work with and manage vendors as applicable, including defining work you're doing, assessing RFPs, driving timelines in partnership with technology teams and ongoing vendor relationship management. 
 Effective socialization of timeline, backlog and priorities to all business partners at varying levels throughout the organization 
 Creating innovative ways to generate and drive user adoption 
 Partner effectively as the Product Owner of an agile squad, including learning and sharing standard methodologies with other POs, and partnering with team members of the squad including the Scrum Master, developers, content writers and designers to develop a best in class experience 
 Manage and/or matrix manage shared User Acceptance Test resources 
 The Skills You Bring 
 5+ years of relative experience 
 Minimum BA/BS degree 
 Exceptional project management skills, with experience delivering projects 
 Comfortable working under pressure in a fast-paced, cross-functional environment 
 Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the ability to present to leadership & business partners and process feedback constructively 
 Collaborative teammate and desire to have fun is essential 
 Experience working in an Agile/Scrum environment is a nice to have 
 Experience working in the financial services industry is a nice to have 
